name: Tetulia Jami Mosque
description: Tetulia Shahi Mosque, is located in village of Tetulia (or Tentulia) in Tala Upazila in the district of Satkhira in Bangladesh. The founder of the mosque was Khan Bahadur Maulvi Qazi Salamatullah Khan, of the zamindar (feudal-lord) Qazi family of Tetulia. The six-domed mosque was built Mughal style in 1858â€“59 and resembles those built by Tipu Sultan's descendants. The founder of the mosque also founded the mansion known as Salam Manzil (now in ruins) and is located in the vicinity of the mosque.
